cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MA 

This paper deals with wireless communication and optimization of power allocation to minimize packet drop rate under average power constraints. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also utilizes tools from optimization and control theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm and evaluates its performance, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
